# 🚀 Day 28/90 – Building the MVP Roadmap

Welcome to **Day 28!**

You've now completed the planning phase of your Blood Report Analyzer.

So far we've designed:

* ✅ Day 21 – Problem Statement
* ✅ Day 22 – User Experience
* ✅ Day 23 – Data Model
* ✅ Day 24 – App Architecture
* ✅ Day 25 – Technology Stack
* ✅ Day 26 – AI Engine
* ✅ Day 27 – Security & Privacy

Today we'll answer one of the biggest questions:

> **"In what order should we build the app?"**

A common mistake is trying to build everything at once. Successful teams build one small, working feature at a time.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll know:

* What to build first
* What can wait until later
* How to break a large project into manageable milestones

---

# Step 1 – Define the MVP

Our first version should do **only these seven things**:

✅ User Registration & Login

✅ Upload Blood Report (PDF/Image)

✅ OCR extracts blood test values

✅ AI explains the report

✅ Save every report

✅ View report history

✅ Compare reports

If these work well, we already have a useful product.

---

# Step 2 – Break the MVP into Phases

Instead of one huge project, divide it into small milestones.

```text
Phase 1
↓

User Accounts

↓

Phase 2
↓

Upload Reports

↓

Phase 3
↓

OCR

↓

Phase 4
↓

AI Analysis

↓

Phase 5
↓

History

↓

Phase 6
↓

Comparison

↓

Version 1 Launch
```

Each phase should be completed before moving to the next.

---

# Phase 1 – User Accounts

Features:

* Register
* Login
* Logout
* Forgot Password (optional for MVP)

Success criteria:

A user can create an account and log in.

---

# Phase 2 – Upload Reports

Features:

* Select PDF
* Select Image
* Upload to cloud storage

Success criteria:

The uploaded file is stored successfully.

---

# Phase 3 – OCR

Features:

* Read uploaded report
* Extract blood test values
* Allow user to review extracted values

Success criteria:

The app correctly extracts the important blood test parameters.

---

# Phase 4 – AI Analysis

Features:

* Explain each blood test
* Generate an overall summary
* Provide general lifestyle suggestions

Success criteria:

The explanation is easy to understand and clearly states that it is not a medical diagnosis.

---

# Phase 5 – Report History

Features:

* Display all uploaded reports
* Sort by date
* Open any previous report

Success criteria:

Users can access every report they have uploaded.

---

# Phase 6 – Compare Reports

Features:

Compare:

* Hemoglobin
* HbA1c
* Vitamin D
* Other available tests

Success criteria:

Users can see how their values change over time.

---

# Phase 7 – Testing

Before launching, check:

* Can users register?
* Can users upload reports?
* Does OCR work?
* Does AI generate explanations?
* Can reports be reopened?
* Can reports be compared?
* Are reports private?

Only after these tests pass should Version 1 be released.

---

# What We Will NOT Build in Version 1

To keep the MVP simple, we'll postpone these ideas:

* Family accounts
* Doctor chat
* Medicine reminders
* Lab integrations
* Smartwatch integration
* Health insurance features
* Appointment booking
* Voice assistant
* AI chatbot

These will become Version 2 or Version 3 features.

