# 👨‍🏫 Mentor's Note

This is a milestone in your learning journey.

On Day 1, you were learning how to print text in Python. By Day 28, you're thinking like a product manager and startup founder—planning features, prioritizing work, and defining what should and shouldn't be part of the first release.

One suggestion for our roadmap is to include a **feedback phase immediately after launch**. Even if Version 1 isn't perfect, getting a small group of real users to try it will teach us far more than months of guessing. Their feedback should guide Version 2, ensuring that we build features people actually need rather than features we only assume they want.
